  <h1>Cluster Headache Tracker</h1>
  <p class="subtitle">A Clinical Tool for Tracking and Managing Cluster Headaches</p>

  <div class="highlight-box">
    <h3>Key Benefits for Clinicians</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Evidence-Based Treatment Decisions:</strong> Access to detailed attack frequency, duration, intensity, and treatment response data</li>
      <li><strong>Objective Documentation:</strong> Standardized reports for insurance authorization of oxygen therapy and other treatments</li>
      <li><strong>Improved Patient Compliance:</strong> Greater patient engagement through digital tracking</li>
      <li><strong>Efficient Appointments:</strong> Pre-formatted reports allow for more meaningful consultation time</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2>Clinical Utility</h2>
  <p>Cluster Headache Tracker provides a structured approach to monitoring this debilitating condition, offering accurate and comprehensive data that supports clinical decision-making and treatment plan development.</p>

  <div class="two-column">
    <div class="column">
      <h3>Data Collection Parameters</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Temporal Patterns:</strong> Precise attack timing, duration, and circadian rhythm analysis</li>
        <li><strong>Pain Intensity:</strong> Standardized 1-10 pain scale</li>
        <li><strong>Associated Symptoms:</strong> Tracking of autonomic features</li>
        <li><strong>Trigger Identification:</strong> Common and patient-specific triggers</li>
        <li><strong>Treatment Response:</strong> Medication effectiveness and oxygen usage</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="column">
      <h3>Visualized Reports for Clinical Use</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Attack Frequency Charts:</strong> Daily/weekly/monthly patterns</li>
        <li><strong>Cluster Period Analysis:</strong> Identification of bout patterns</li>
        <li><strong>Treatment Response Metrics:</strong> Measuring intervention efficacy</li>
        <li><strong>Trigger Correlation:</strong> Statistical associations with potential triggers</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

